{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/paperfaces/jonathanhagans-portrait/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Winter faces","date":"2013-12-16T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"December 16th, 2013","date_from_now":"6 years ago","last_modified_at":null,"last_modified_at_from_now":null,"path":"/paperfaces/jonathanhagans-portrait/","author":null,"excerpt":"PaperFaces portrait commission drawn with Paper for iOS on an iPad.","tags":["portrait","illustration","Paper for iOS"],"image":null,"toc":null,"comments":null,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"578381ad-60d3-56af-ada5-77b27ced079c","html":"<p>I don’t often draw faces, but with the right photo reference I sometimes attempt it. </p>\n<p>To build up values in the faces I used the pencil tool exclusively — adding shadows and shading before applying watercolor. Usually I do the opposite by applying a watercolor base first and then penciling over to refine. Quite happy with how everything turned out.</p>\n<p>PaperFaces portrait commission for <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jonathanhagans\">@jonathanhagans</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-jonathanhagans-process-1-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-jonathanhagans-process-2-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-jonathanhagans-process-3-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-jonathanhagans-process-4-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><strong>Tools used:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B009K448L4/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&#x26;camp=1789&#x26;creative=390957&#x26;creativeASIN=B009K448L4&#x26;linkCode=as2&#x26;tag=mademist-20\">Pogo Connect Bluetooth Smart Pen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://paper.bywetransfer.com/\">Paper for iOS</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"I don’t often draw faces, but with the right p